excerpt: Modern waterfront building housing artefacts from 50,000 years of Australian history & culture.
detail_description: The National Museum of Australia is a modern waterfront building that showcases artifacts spanning 50,000 years of Australian history and culture. It is one of the top sightseeing attractions in the area, offering fun activities for visitors. The museum features free exhibitions like 'Great Southern Land,' which explores the essence of Australian identity, and the Gandel Atrium filled with captivating objects. Families can enjoy the Tim and Gina Fairfax Discovery Centre with interactive activities and virtual storytelling.
name: National Museum of Australia

excerpt: Serene trails for walking & cycling border this scenic man-made lake offering boating & fishing.
detail_description: Lake Burley Griffin, located in Canberra, offers serene trails for walking and cycling along its scenic man-made shores. It's a popular spot for boating and fishing. The area is also home to some of Canberra's most sought-after wedding venues, including the Old Parliament House, Rose Garden, Gold Creek Chapel, Margaret Whitlam Pavilion overlooking the National Arboretum, National Gallery Sculpture Garden, and The Boat House.
name: Lake Burley Griffin

excerpt: Children's museum featuring interactive exhibits & puppet shows about science & technology.
detail_description: Questacon - National Science and Technology Centre is a children's museum that offers interactive exhibits and puppet shows focused on science and technology. It is one of the must-visit attractions in Canberra, along with other notable sites like the National Gallery of Australia, Australian War Memorial, and more. The center provides an engaging experience for visitors to immerse themselves in scientific exploration.
name: Questacon - National Science and Technology Centre
address: King Edward Terrace, Parkes ACT 2600, Australia

detail_description: Parliament House in Canberra offers a unique experience for visitors and their furry friends. The expansive lawns in front of the building, known as The Great Verandah, are open to both humans and dogs. Capture the perfect dog-selfie against the backdrop of this iconic political landmark for a memorable memento of your visit.
name: Parliament house

excerpt: Public library with a reading room, treasures gallery, changing exhibitions, a bookshop and a cafe.
detail_description: The National Library of Australia in Canberra is a public library that offers a variety of attractions, including a reading room, treasures gallery, changing exhibitions, bookshop, and cafe. Visitors can immerse themselves in the country's rich collections by also exploring nearby cultural institutions such as the National Gallery of Australia and Australian War Memorial.
name: National Library of Australia
address: Parkes Pl W, Canberra ACT 2600, Australia

detail_description: Telstra Tower, standing at 195 meters high, is a prominent landmark offering breathtaking views of Canberra, particularly at night. The tower features a gallery providing insights into Australia's telecommunications history and the tower's construction. While parking in the area may be average, Telstra Tower remains a must-visit destination for tourists and an excellent workplace.
name: Telstra

excerpt: Works by Aboriginal & Torres Strait Islander people in a museum of traditional & modern art.
detail_description: The Canberra Museum & Gallery is a captivating blend of traditional and contemporary art, showcasing works by Aboriginal & Torres Strait Islander artists. The National Portrait Gallery within the museum features over 400 portraits of influential figures who have shaped Australia's history and culture. One of its highlights is the permanent exhibition of Sidney Nolan paintings, offering insight into the artist's personal journey to critical acclaim. Housed in an elegant art-deco building, the museum also preserves Australian moving-picture and sound archives.
name: Canberra Museum & Gallery

excerpt: Audiovisual archive with a wide array of works, from experimental films to oral histories.
detail_description: The National Film and Sound Archive of Australia (NFSA) is a treasure trove of over 2 million audiovisual works, ranging from experimental films to oral histories. It's renowned for its collection and restoration of recordings that capture Australian history. Housed in the former Australian Institute of Anatomy, the museum offers a nostalgic journey through decades of professional preservation with engaging events and exhibitions. The Game Masters Exhibition is a must-visit, offering an immersive experience that brings childhood memories back to life.
name: National Film and Sound Archive of Australia (NFSA)

detail_description: The National Science and Technology Centre is a fascinating destination for science enthusiasts of all ages. Visitors can engage in interactive exhibits, hands-on experiments, and immersive experiences that showcase the wonders of science and technology. The center offers a diverse range of educational programs and workshops, making it an ideal spot for school field trips and family outings. With its engaging displays and informative presentations, the National Science and Technology Centre provides an enriching experience that sparks curiosity and learning in its visitors.
name: National Science And Technology Centre
address: King Edward Terrace, Parkes ACT 2600, Australia

excerpt: Long-standing shopping destination with 260+ shops, restaurants & services, plus a cinema.
detail_description: Canberra Centre is a well-established shopping destination featuring over 260 shops, restaurants, and services along with a cinema. The city's layout was meticulously planned by a single architect, resulting in an abundance of green spaces and open areas. Canberra also boasts a thriving wine region with more than 30 wineries within a short drive from the city, offering opportunities to meet vignerons and sample local creations.
name: Canberra Centre

excerpt: Popular visitor center featuring educational exhibits on how Canberra was designed & a city diorama.
detail_description: The National Capital Exhibition is a popular visitor center in Canberra, offering educational exhibits on the city's design and a diorama of the city. Founded over a century ago, Canberra has its own unique culture and history. Visitors have found the museum to be small but well-designed, packed with information about Canberra's history and layout. The staff are friendly and knowledgeable, and admission is free. The exhibition also features artifacts, pictures, and information about the city's history.
name: National Capital Exhibition

excerpt: Plays and music in a modern building with 3 venues ranging from large and historic to intimate.
detail_description: Located in the heart of Canberra, the Canberra Theatre Centre offers a modern building with three venues catering to various audience sizes. From large and historic to intimate, this premier performing arts venue hosts a wide range of entertainment options, from classic plays by Bell Shakespeare and performances by the Australian Ballet to contemporary shows and concerts. It's a must-visit for those looking for world-class live entertainment experiences in Australia's creative capital.
name: Canberra Theatre Centre
address: Civic Square, London Cct, Canberra ACT 2601, Australia

detail_description: Located in Canberra, the CSIRO Discovery Centre is a modern and interactive facility that offers a range of exciting exhibitions and hands-on STEM activities. It utilizes cutting-edge technology like virtual and augmented reality to make science accessible to visitors of all levels of scientific understanding. The center also hosts subject-specific workshops for science students, mapping outcomes to the curriculum. With helpful staff who are knowledgeable about their field, the center engages students in learning experiences through workshops such as robotics and DNA exploration, tailored for different age groups.
name: CSIRO Discovery Centre
address: N Science Rd, Acton ACT 2601, Australia

excerpt: University-affiliated gallery showcasing the work of contemporary regional & international artists.
detail_description: The Drill Hall Gallery, affiliated with the Australian National University, offers an intimate and enriching experience for art enthusiasts. Originally a training center for soldiers during WWII, it now showcases major works by prominent contemporary regional and international artists. The gallery is known for its impressive Sidney Nolan's 9-panel panorama, Riverbend. With a rich history dating back to 1940, the building was superbly remodeled in 1984 to create a beautiful art space.
name: Drill Hall Gallery

excerpt: Canberra is Australia’s capital, inland from the country's southeast coast. Surrounded by forest, farmland and nature reserves, it earns its nickname, the "Bush Capital.” The city's focal point is Lake Burley Griffin, filled with sailboats and kayaks. On the lakeshore is the massive, strikingly modern Parliament House, as well as museums including the National Gallery, known for its indigenous art collections.
detail_description: Canberra, Australia's capital, is nestled inland from the southeast coast and surrounded by lush forests, farmlands, and nature reserves. It's known as the 'Bush Capital' due to its natural surroundings. The city revolves around Lake Burley Griffin, where sailboats and kayaks dot the waters. Along the lake sits the strikingly modern Parliament House and museums like the National Gallery, renowned for its indigenous art collections.
name: Canberra

detail_description: Ferry Gate, Floriade is a month-long flower festival in Australia that showcases over one million bulbs planted in beautiful garden beds, creating stunning displays of color. The event offers gardening demonstrations by experts and also features evening concerts, movies, and dance parties among the flowers. Visitors can enjoy the vibrant tulip blooms during the spring season and appreciate the smooth organization and excellent presentation of the festival.
name: Ferry Gate, Floriade

detail_description: Nestled in the Melbourne Building, Bar Rochford is a popular local spot celebrated for its exceptional food, diverse wine selection, and inviting ambiance. The establishment boasts a dynamic team that consistently updates the menus to showcase seasonal ingredients and create innovative dishes. The venue's industrial-chic space sets the stage for a lively atmosphere complemented by an eclectic vinyl soundtrack.
name: Bar Rochford

detail_description: Commonwealth Park in Canberra is a must-visit destination, especially during the annual Floriade festival held in September and October. The park offers beautiful strolls, historical exhibitions, and picturesque views of Lake Burley Griffin. Visitors can enjoy the extensive displays of flowering bulbs, artistic sculptures, and entertainment events. Whether it's a leisurely walk along the lake shores or a picnic on the grassy spots, Commonwealth Park provides a delightful experience for all ages.
name: Commonwealth Park

detail_description: BentSpoke Brewing Co. is a lively, two-story craft brewery located in the heart of Braddon, Canberra. It's a popular spot for post-work drinks and casual meetups, offering a variety of beers including the Barley Griffin Australian pale ale. Visitors can enjoy a sample paddle to taste a selection of their best brews and pair them with delicious food options like smoked mac n cheese balls, steak sandwiches, and chicken schnitzels.
name: BentSpoke Brewing Co.

excerpt: Braddon is a hip area where artisan coffee roasters, offbeat cafes, and innovative Modern Australian restaurants occupy renovated industrial buildings on and around Lonsdale Street. Quirky stores in the cutting-edge Ori and Nibu x Palko residential developments sell indie fashion, gourmet groceries, and one-off homewares. The neighbourhood is also home to Gorman Arts Centre and small performing arts theatres.
detail_description: Braddon is a trendy neighborhood known for its artisan coffee shops, unique cafes, and modern Australian dining spots housed in refurbished industrial buildings along Lonsdale Street. The area also features unconventional boutiques within the Ori and Nibu x Palko residential developments, offering indie fashion, specialty groceries, and distinctive home goods. Additionally, Braddon is home to the Gorman Arts Centre and intimate performing arts venues.
name: Braddon

detail_description: Haig Park Village Markets is a charming outdoor market located in Haig Park in Braddon, open on Sundays from 8:30am to 2pm. The market offers a delightful array of food and fresh produce, making it perfect for families. Visitors can explore numerous stalls offering sweet pastries, breads, BBQed treats, and multicultural foods. Additionally, there are locally handmade items available for purchase, including beautifully designed candles and botanical face cream.
name: Haig Park Village Markets

detail_description: Canberra Wine and Spirit Merchants is a highly praised establishment in the renowned cool-climate wine region of Canberra. Visitors appreciate the personalized service, with John being particularly commended for his prompt and personal assistance in locating specific wines. The store offers a great range of wines, including champagnes from smaller houses, and also provides recommendations for nearby spots to enjoy an afternoon drink. Customers have had positive experiences interacting with the owner while making purchases, receiving valuable suggestions on wine selections.
name: Canberra Wine and Spirit Merchants

excerpt: Compact casino featuring multiple playing areas & a poker lounge, plus a sports bar & an eatery.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Australia’s capital, Casino Canberra offers a vibrant gaming experience that perfectly complements the city’s lush surroundings. This compact yet stylish venue features multiple gaming areas and a dedicated poker lounge, making it an ideal spot for both seasoned players and newcomers alike. The casino also boasts a lively sports bar and an eatery where you can refuel after an exhilarating game.
name: Casino Canberra

detail_description: Lonsdale St, located in Braddon, owes much of its revitalization to the efforts of designer and developer Nik Bulum. He kickstarted the transformation with Lonsdale Street Traders, a pop-up space that offered affordable rents to up-and-coming creatives, fostering a culture of flexibility. This initiative gained momentum and inspired Bulum to pursue more lasting enhancements for the area.
name: Lonsdale St

detail_description: GoBoat Canberra (Central) offers a fantastic experience for exploring the city from a different perspective. The central location makes it easily accessible with convenient parking. The staff is friendly and helpful, providing great suggestions for routes and making the whole process easy. Whether you're looking for a fun group activity or a romantic date, cruising on the lake with delicious food and good company is highly recommended. Additionally, the dog-friendly policy allows you to bring your furry friend along for an enjoyable ride on the water.
name: GoBoat Canberra (Central)
address: Queen Elizabeth Terrace, Parkes ACT 2600, Australia

detail_description: Dave's Tours Canberra offers a full-day tour that takes you to various attractions in the area, including wineries, chocolate shops, and gin/vodka distilleries. The tour is jam-packed with visits to 5 different places from 9:30 am to 4:30 pm. Visitors have the opportunity to explore a vast collection of war artifacts and personal stories at the museum and memorial honoring Australian soldiers' sacrifices.
name: Dave's Tours Canberra

detail_description: Glebe Park in Canberra, known for its stylish self-contained apartments and convenient amenities such as an outdoor pool and fitness centre, offers a peaceful retreat. Situated just 200 metres from the National Convention Centre, the park provides spacious green surroundings adorned with beautiful elm trees that transform into a delightful golden hue during autumn. With a children's playground and numerous paved pathways for leisurely strolls, Glebe Park is the ideal escape from city life.
name: Glebe Park

detail_description: The Australian Academy of Science, established in 1954 and located in Canberra, is housed in a stunning architectural marvel known as the Shine Dome. This renowned institution hosts various events such as guest lectures, symposiums, seminars, and features a gallery for enthusiasts. It is dedicated to advancing sciences through global programs and regular cutting-edge science lectures. The committed and professional staff ensures an exceptional experience for visitors.
name: Australian Academy of Science
address: Ian Potter House, 9 Gordon St, Canberra ACT 2601, Australia

detail_description: The Australian National Korean War Memorial is a significant site located in ANZAC Park. It commemorates the 17,000 Australians who fought in the Korean War under the United Nations Command from 1950 to 1953. The memorial honors and remembers those who served and died during this conflict. Visitors can observe plaques with historical information about the war and pay their respects to the brave individuals who endured harsh conditions while defending freedom.
name: Australian National Korean War Memorial

excerpt: Stone cottage from around 1860, now a museum on its former residents & life on the Limestone Plains.
detail_description: Blundells Cottage, a charming stone structure dating back to 1860, offers a glimpse into the lives of early Canberra residents. Constructed with stone from Mt Ainslie, this historic museum is open on Saturdays from 10am to 2pm. While its limited opening hours may pose a challenge for some visitors, the cottage's exterior and informative boards provide an intriguing peek into the past.
name: Blundells Cottage

excerpt: Funky Pan-Asian eatery offering a raw bar, bao burgers & small plates, plus hearty homestyle mains.
detail_description: Lazy Su is a funky Pan-Asian restaurant that offers a blend of Korean, Japanese, and American cuisine. The restaurant's design and menu reflect a casual yet stylish dining experience with retro chic decor and an extensive menu featuring small plates, bao burgers, raw bar options, and hearty homestyle mains. Located on the lively Lonsdale Street strip, Lazy Su has mastered the art of American-Japanese-Korean retro restaurant culture.
name: Lazy Su

excerpt: Upscale menu, including antipasti and handcut pasta, in a smart restaurant with a playful vibe.
detail_description: Italian and Sons is a trendy restaurant that has been a staple in the Braddon area for over a decade. The upscale menu features antipasti and hand-cut pasta, creating a playful vibe within the smart establishment. Despite its popularity among date-nighters, birthday celebrants, and Canberra's social elite, some have expressed disappointment with the food and service quality.
name: Italian and Sons

excerpt: Modern sushi bar with dishes made from locally sourced ingredients, plus an extensive drinks menu.
detail_description: Raku is a modern sushi bar that offers dishes made from locally sourced ingredients and an extensive drinks menu. It has a sleek design and serves modern Japanese fare, making it one of the top sushi restaurants in the area. The restaurant is known for its delicious food and always delivers a unique dining experience. Raku's popularity is evident as it has been recognized alongside other notable dining establishments in the region.
name: Raku
address: Shop DG36C/148 Bunda St, Canberra ACT 2601, Australia

excerpt: Trendy eatery in a sleek setting serving Southeast Asian dishes with a twist, plus cocktails & beer.
detail_description: Zaab is a trendy restaurant that offers a contemporary take on Southeast Asian cuisine, specifically Lao and Thai dishes. The sleek setting and vibrant atmosphere make it an ideal spot for enjoying a modern twist on traditional flavors. The menu features options like the vegetarian Feed menu, which offers an intense and delicious dining experience perfect for sharing with friends. Additionally, the al a carte menu includes plenty of vegetarian choices, including the famous Betel Leaf dish.
name: Zaab

detail_description: Rizla, located in the vibrant Braddon area, is a unique winebarstaurant that offers an exceptional dining experience. Owned by Andy Day, this establishment focuses on Riesling and offers a variety of regional red and white varietals. The set menu is reasonably priced and provides generous portions, making it ideal for group dining. Customers have praised the well-considered portion sizes and highlighted the delicious mushroom main dish.
name: Rizla
address: unit 146 Mode3/24 Lonsdale St, Braddon ACT 2612, Australia

detail_description: Kingpin Canberra offers a diverse range of entertainment options, making it more than just a bowling alley. Visitors can enjoy activities such as laser tag, escape rooms, arcade games, karaoke, table tennis, and virtual reality experiences. The venue also features fully licensed bars and curated food menus. Recognized as Canberra's Favourite Entertainment Venue in 2020, Kingpin provides an ideal setting for family outings with its friendly staff and relaxed atmosphere.
name: Kingpin Canberra

excerpt: Easygoing hangout specialising in substantial portions of BBQ & chicken specialties.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Canberra's CBD, Terra Canberra is a refreshing twist on the traditional dining experience. This vibrant eatery specializes in hearty BBQ and chicken dishes, making it an ideal spot for breakfast and lunch enthusiasts. With its focus on produce-driven meals, guests can indulge in a variety of smoked meats straight from the spit, gourmet rolls, seasonal roasted veggies, fresh salads, and invigorating juices.
name: Terra Canberra
address: Unit 4/115 Marcus Clarke St, Canberra ACT 2601, Australia

excerpt: Public, campus-based higher education and research institution, founded in 1946, with a law faculty.
detail_description: The Australian National University, established in 1946, is a prestigious public research university with a renowned law faculty. Situated at the heart of Canberra, the campus offers easy access to the city's new tram system and boasts modern infrastructure and well-maintained facilities. The university features various on-campus shops and provides a peaceful environment for both work and study. With its rich history and breathtaking views, including those of the Observatory and valley, it offers an inspiring setting for academic pursuits.
name: The Australian National University

detail_description: Lennox Gardens, located on the shore of Lake Burley Griffin in Canberra, offers a picturesque setting for picnics and leisure activities. Visitors can enjoy a pleasant walk to Beijing Gardens and Nara Peace Park, making it an ideal spot to visit during the autumn or spring seasons. The gardens provide various attractions such as interesting sculptures and plantings, although there is a lack of botanical labels.
name: Lennox Gardens

detail_description: The Captain Cook Memorial Jet, erected in 1970 to commemorate the bicentenary of James Cook's arrival, is a prominent feature near Regatta Point. This iconic water column can be seen from various spots around Lake Burley Griffin and is particularly striking when illuminated. Visitors can enjoy picnics on the surrounding grassy areas and even rent paddle boats for a fun day out with family and friends.
name: Captain Cook Memorial Jet

detail_description: Reconciliation Place is a must-visit spot, especially during the annual Enlighten event. The Night Noodle Market and Balloon festival are popular attractions here, offering great opportunities to enjoy with friends. The venue is also perfect for leisurely strolls and picnics, thanks to its beautiful lake views and spacious grassy areas. Visitors can capture stunning photos while taking in the serene atmosphere of this place.
name: Reconciliation Place
address: Queen Elizabeth Terrace, Parkes ACT 2600, Australia

detail_description: City Walk Centre, also known as Civic or CBD, is the bustling heart of Canberra, Australia's capital. Established in 1927, it features a grid-like street layout flanked by impressive early 20th-century buildings and lush greenery. Visitors can enjoy a leisurely morning stroll during autumn to experience the contrast between the city's lively atmosphere and its tranquil ambiance. The area offers an array of attractions and activities, making it a popular destination for tourists.
name: City Walk Centre

detail_description: Braddon Merchant is a 5-star rated restaurant with excellent food and service. It consistently receives great reviews from its customers, who enjoy the outdoor seating as well.
name: Braddon Merchant

detail_description: Canberra Olympic Pool is a popular spot, especially for teenagers who are drawn to the city's only diving board. The facility includes a 50-meter and 25-meter heated pools, making it an ideal destination for swimming enthusiasts. Visitors have praised the pleasant experience of swimming in the pool, with perfect water temperature and convenient amenities such as heaters in the change rooms. Additionally, there are plans to return during summer to take advantage of all-day relaxation by exploring other pools including a diving pool.
name: Canberra Olympic Pool
Palace Electric Cinemas
address: 2 Phillip Law St, Canberra ACT 2601, Australia

detail_description: INTRA PRVN is a unique and fun addition to the Canberra cafe scene, known for its quality coffee and minimalist yet aesthetic interior. The house-blend Staple offers a rich blend of vanilla and hazelnut with stonefruit overtones. The staff provides friendly service, and customers enjoy the muffins from Sonoma as well as the house blend coffee available for takeaway. The cafe has both indoor and outdoor seating, offering a limited brunch-style menu with sweet treats.
name: INTRA PRVN
POP Canberra
address: Shop G12/27 Lonsdale St, Braddon ACT 2612, Australia

detail_description: Mu Omakase, a Japanese restaurant in Canberra, has quickly gained popularity since its opening in 2021. The restaurant offers a unique dining experience with a fusion of Kaiseki, Robatayaki, and Omakase cuisines. With only 10 seats around the counter, diners are taken on an unforgettable journey through 12 courses prepared by sushi master Shinya Nakano. The intimate setting allows guests to watch the chef prepare mouth-watering dishes right in front of them.
name: Mu

detail_description: The Little Burley Market is a charming Saturday market located by the waterside, offering a delightful experience with its gourmet food and artisan offerings. Visitors can enjoy the picturesque views while indulging in tantalizing food options and exploring locally made goods such as ceramics, jewelry, and art. The market also features an array of international cuisines to savor, including Italian, Vietnamese, Argentinian, and Mexican fare.
name: The Little Burley Market
address: Queen Elizabeth Terrace, Parkes ACT 2600, Australia
